Yesterday, I was honored to welcome Small Business Administrator Kelly Loeffler to Troup County.

We visited Jane (Kimble’s) Foods, which was first started with SBA support.  Later, we hosted a roundtable discussion with Troup County’s business community, and had lunch at historic Charlie Joseph’s.

@SBA_Kelly was the first Cabinet Member to visit our District during President Trump’s second term!

We celebrated history tonight in Columbus, as the Atlanta Braves’ newest minor league affiliate, the Columbus Clingstones, played their very first game at historic Synovus Park — and they walked away with a 3-0 WIN on Opening Night!

And, to top it off, Craig Kimbrel pitched his first inning as a Brave in 11 years!

@GoClingstones!
